metadata.name: Today, I looked up.
metadata.description:
Never quite ready to start the day,  
One moment please! Any excuse to delay,  
The world that awaits me, an endless fray,  
With peace and calm, so far away.

Countless days blend into one,  
More goals completed, yet nothing's done,  
A soul that aches me, what have I won?  
With time against me, I can't outrun. 

Thinking too much leaves me distraught,  
Flames alight and wait to be caught,  
Stop! Drop, and please roll into good thoughts,  
For one brief moment, with time that I've bought.

A lovely warm glow drifts into view,  
Look! Another! A beautiful hue,  
Time be kind, slow this moment for me,  
The leaves are falling, so playful and free.

How did I miss this all before?  
A sky so captivating, hard now to ignore,  
A world of wonders, so easy to find,  
With one look up,  I ease my mind.
